    <subfield code="o">5</subfield>
    <subfield code="m">In one dimension, strong quantum fluctuations prohibit true long-range order. Nevertheless, many 1d Mott insulators, including e.g. the half-filled 1d Hubbard model, develop instead power-law magnetic correlations and still maintain low-energy magnon modes. Such systems are thus close counterparts of higher-dimensional systems with broken spin-rotational invariance</subfield>
